<TITLE> Shanghai to launch `international' TV channel </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Beijing, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Shanghai, China's financial capital, is to launch an English- and Japanese-language television channel on Jan. 1 as part of an effort to become an "international and cultural metropolis", the Xinhua news agency said on Sunday. International Channel Shanghai will cover news, information, fashion, entertainment, foreign TV shows and movies. It will air in English and Japanese, with Chinese captions, for 19 hours a day. "It is expected to serve as a window to showcase the economic and cultural development of Shanghai," Li Ruigang, president of Shanghai Media Group, was quoted as saying. Shanghai TV was the first in China to provide English programmes in 1986. China strictly controls the media and this year urged the country's increasingly freewheeling broadcasters to forgo vulgarity in favour of providing inspiring content for the masses imbued with socialist values. State television already offers one nationwide English-language station which mostly showcases Chinese culture, travel, news and sport
